article.headline: Gonzaga 86, E. Washington 57
article.story: CAREY J. WILLIAMS Associated Press SPOKANE, Wash. -- Steven Gray scored 18 points, all on 3-pointers, as Gonzaga beat Eastern Washington 86-57 on Tuesday night. Robert Sacre and freshman Mathis Monninghoff scored 13 apiece and Sam Dower added 11 for Gonzaga (4-2). The Bulldogs shot 57.9 percent from the field and made 11 of 16 3-pointers. Eastern Washington (1-5) was led by Jeffrey Forbes' 18 points, and Kevin Winford added 11. The Eagles shot 33.9 percent, made 7 of 18 free throws, had 10 assists and were forced into 21 turnovers. Eastern Washington has lost 30 of the last 31 games against its Spokane County neighbor, including 23 straight.
